<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98625623741573></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98625623741573><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=178&mid=98625623741573>An alternate method...</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 2nd 8:03 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's how I got my Trueshot.  This is a different method than most of these posts suggest.  This is for the non-twinks (like myself)who don't have 1000pp to burn getting your fletching up to 165 - or, for that matter, any teens-level ranger who'd rather spend the money upgrading your armor and weaponry.  My ranger is 21st level and the sum total of everything owned in his lifetime is probably less than 1000 plat.  I'd still be wearing armor made out of ruined wolf pelts if I pumped everything I earned into fletching attempts.<br><br>Here we go - starting in West Freeport, give Jyle enough lanterns to get two full stacks of wood chips.  Odds are you'll get a treant heart as well that you can save in the bank for a later time.  Then put everything you don't absolutely need in the bank, load yourself up with small boxes, and wait for the boat.  After zoning into OOT, do the 'kiola dash' at the first dock, buying as many kiola nuts (unstackable) as you can carry.  You should be able to catch the boat again before it leaves with no trouble, but if you don't another one will be along soon.  Use the time to fish (later in life, you might discover that those fish scales come in handy) or practice your conjuration with 'Dance of the Fireflies' (you'll want good conjuration skills so 'Stinging Swarm' actually works when you finally get it).<br><br>Once you get to BB, go into Kaladim and get all the Tumpy Tonics you possibly can from your load of Kiolas, then turn those in to Trantor for dwarven wire.  Depending on how much wire you have, you might opt to go back to the docks and catch another boat for another trip around OOT and more Kiolas.  As before, use the waiting time to boost skills.<br><br>After you have at least two stacks of dwarven wire, head to Steamfont and crush clockworks.  I did this part in my low teens, so I was able to get xp and actually gain a level off the big clockworks.  This part takes a little patience, but try to get two stacks or more of microservos.  I have gotten 4 drops in a row, then gone 15 without one, but in due time you'll have plenty.<br><br>At this point, head over to Kelethin.  You will still need spiderling silk, but considering the abundance of spiderlings in Gfay that will not be a problem.  You may find that some of the merchants near the lifts have some to sell to you.<br>Once you are finished collecting materials, go the the ranger guild with your fletching kit and pull up a chair next to Maesyn...if you have gathered at least two stacks of wire and microservos and one stack of wood chips, you will have at least 20 attempts to make a Trueshot.<br><br>I got my Trueshot at level 14, with an 85 wisdom.  70 fletching (not a typo - SEVENTY). Second attempt.<br><br>Yes, I know I was very lucky.  But suppose you have maybe a 7% - 10% chance of success (nobody knows what the actual percentage really is at the varying levels) you are very likely to be successful with 20 (or more) attempts.  The cost associated with getting enough materials for 20 -40 attempts and a 70 fletching skill is many hundreds of platinum less than getting a 165+ fletching.  Even if not for my good fortune, I fully expect I would have crafted a bow long before my materials ran out.<br><br>Granted, 165 fletching skill will be it's own reward in due time, and I plan on getting there myself when I'm high level and have platinum falling out of my pockets.  But the point of this post is that, considering the low cost and relative ease in obtaining the bowstave ingredients many times over, the cost, time, and effort associated with achieving god-level fletching skill is not necessary to craft a Trueshot.    <br><br>Good luck, safe travels, and let me know how it goes.<br><br>Greybear<br>21st Ranger<br>Xev<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
