	   <tr><td colspan=2> This is exactly how i got mine (see post entitled Iaeuvas of Luclin) I did it untwinked and at level 8 with a fletching skill of 24.  The only hang up to doing it at this low a level is that some of the common spawns in steamfront still conned yellow/red to me. I died twice in the gathering of a full stack of the micro-servos, but in the end i succeeded on my second try also.  My total cost was half a bubble of exp for the two deaths and about 7pp for several lanterns and the water needed for tumpy tonics.  I definately recommend this to any low to mid level ranger.  The trueshot sure makes snare kiting (once you get level 9) alot more effective.<br><br>             Iaeuvas of Luclin (Knights of the<br>                                 White Order)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
